.TH CWE-59 7 "2025-12-11" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-59 \- Improper Link Resolution Before File Access ('Link Following')
.SH RANK
KEV\-referenced weakness. Not part of the 2025 CWE Top 25; documented here because it appears in the CISA KEV catalog.
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: KEV\-referenced weakness.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The product attempts to access a file based on the filename, but it does not properly prevent that filename from identifying a link or shortcut that resolves to an unintended resource.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-15): \fB16\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
CVE\-2019\-0841, CVE\-2019\-1064, CVE\-2019\-1069, CVE\-2019\-1129, CVE\-2019\-1130, CVE\-2019\-1253, CVE\-2019\-1315, CVE\-2019\-1385, CVE\-2020\-0787, CVE\-2020\-36193, CVE\-2022\-30333, CVE\-2023\-36874, CVE\-2025\-21391, CVE\-2025\-48384, CVE\-2025\-60710, CVE\-2026\-41091.
.SH EXAMPLES
One vulnerable\->fixed pair per ecosystem (Python).
.SS Python
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
open(path, "w").write(data)        # follows an attacker-planted symlink
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
fd = os.open(path, os.O_WRONLY | os.O_CREAT | os.O_NOFOLLOW | os.O_EXCL, 0o600)
os.write(fd, data)
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcwe\fR(7) (index).
.PP
